  "name": "Antarctic 88S dense (ICESat-2 turning-latitude stress target)",
  "note": "Near the +/-88 deg turning latitude, ICESat-2 ground-track density peaks, so the densest shard here is far heavier than NEON's 44-59 granules. HEALPix is CRS-agnostic; a rectilinear analog would need a polar CRS (e.g. EPSG:3031). See issues #121 / #148. The ring is a MultiPolygon of eight 45-deg sectors with vertices sampled every 1 deg of longitude: a single lat/lon rectangle spanning -180..180 degenerates under spherical polygon fill (mortie traces its edges as great circles, collapsing the ring to an antimeridian sliver -- 10 cells instead of ~576 at o9).",
